cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper proposes a framework for training and inference of neural networks that addresses the problem of resource limitations on edge devices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention modules and knowledge distillation, which are techniques commonly used in neural network optimization and compression, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
